The intraspecific variation in the type of intestinal loops observed in Platevindex luteus ( type I, type II and intermediary between types I and II) is very unusual. Nearly all onchidiid species are characterized by only one type of intestinal loops. Another known exception is Alionchis jailoloensis characterized by intestinal loops of both types II and III (
Goulding et al . 2018a
;
Dayrat et al . 2019c
). The dissection of individuals for which the species identification was confirmed through DNA sequences allowed us to determine that intestinal types vary between individuals of P. luteus even at the exact same localities.
